         <abstract>
            <p>The a priori evaluation of the pointwise approximation, by a regularization method suggested earlier, of a L&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; periodic function f, when only noisy Fourier coefficients of f are known, is given here in a formulation more suitable for numerical verification. A careful evaluation of the constants involved in the formulas is also provided. Finally, a procedure is described of a statistical check performed in order to verify whether the theoretically suggested value of the regularization parameter is a good choice with respect to functions generally arising in applications.</p>
          </abstract>
